author: COMSOL
description:
This example of turbulent flow in a partially baffled turbulent mixer with a three-bladed impeller shows how to set up the Rotating Machinery, Turbulent Flow interfaces from the Mixer Module with a Level Set method for free surface flow in a rotating geometry. A time-dependent simulation is performed and the vortex generated by the rotating fluid can be observed.

NOTE: The time-dependent study can take about a day to solve and generate approximately 3Â GB of data.
